        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 1:28PM EDT until June 8 at 1:45PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 127 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Elkton to near Chadbourn to Green Sea, moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Whiteville, Tabor City, Chadbourn, Bethel, Lake Waccamaw, Fair Bluff,
Boardman, Hallsboro, Nakina, Cherry Grove, Redbug, Old Dock, Mollie,
Sidney, Southeastern Community College, Clarendon, Williams,
Evergreen, Crusoe Island, and Green Sea.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please send your reports of hail and/or wind damage, including trees
or large limbs downed, by calling the National Weather Service office
in Wilmington at 1-800-697-3901.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
